		<h1>Research Assistant </h1>
		
		<p>The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System regularly hires research assistants who apply quantitative skills both to   real-world policy issues and to high-level research projects. </p>
		<p>This is a two-year term  position, after which research assistants go on to graduate programs or  careers in economics, business, or related disciplines.</p>
		<p>Research assistants are employed in several of the Board's divisions. Follow the links below for job qualifications in the various divisions and the   procedures for submitting an application: </p>
		
          <div>
              <ul>
                <li><a href="ra_research.htm">Economic research divisions</a> (International Finance, Monetary Affairs, Research and Statistics, and the Office of  Financial Stability) <br />

                  &nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="howtoApplyRAecon.htm">To apply</a> </li>
                <li><a href="ra_cca.htm">The Division of Consumer and Community Affairs</a>
                </li>
                <li><a href="ra_rbops.htm">The Division of Reserve Bank Operations and<br />Payment   Systems</a> </li>
              </ul> 
			 <p>Our brochure, <a href="pdf/RA_Brochure.pdf" target="_blank">Open Doors to a Bright Future: Research Assistant Positions at the Federal Reserve Board, Washington, D.C. (4.53 MB PDF)</a>, tells you more about the Federal Reserve and its mission, and discusses the great opportunities and benefits of being a research assistant at the Board.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>

